examples.en: Mercury is the smallest of all the planets.
The camera could define the smallest object.
They are unforgiving of the smallest mistake.
Even the smallest movement made him cry out in pain.
It is extremely brittle, chipping on the smallest fall or shock.
Try and take off the smallest possible shaves.
I couldn't offer her even the smallest ray of comfort.
I was, as you rightly said, the smallest boy in the class.
One "bit" is the smallest amount of data which can exist, and corresponds to the answer to a yes-or-no question.
He beats his children for even the smallest misdemeanour.
The smallest mischance could spell disaster for our plan.
The smallest contribution will be thankfully received.
The smallest pond at night mirrors the firmament above.
A hummingbird is the smallest, most ethereal and daintiest of birds.
